I print, inspect, and package all my art in my home studio in Central Florida. Nothing is mass-produced.
The Quality You Expect from Hand-Crafted Art Prints

All my prints are created using acid-free, archival quality paper that has a subtle canvas texture, which adds depth and detail not normally found in photo paper. I use a Canon wide-format printer with Canon inks to deliver pure, rich colors and superior longevity.

These beautiful prints come ready to frame using 11X14 frames found right here on Amazon or at your local big box store, allowing you to easily match the frames to your decor. Need to cover a larger wall area? Use a larger frame with a wide border mat. This works fabulously and looks great.

Each set is carefully packaged by hand in a clear protective, archival poly sleeve, along with a thick backing board for added rigidity and placed in an eco-friendly Stay-Flat mailer. Not only does this packaging protect your prints during transit, but it’s suitable for gift giving as is!

Art prints make great gifts for any occasion- Mother’s Day, Birthday, Baby Showers, Wedding, House Warming, Father’s Day, etc. From elegant, to the quirky, to inspirational, there is something for everyone.
